title: Somerset Patriots' playoff game rained out
text:
Somerset Patriots' playoff game rained out Justin Antwell, Somerset Patriots 3:57 p.m. EDT October 2, 2015 The Somerset Patriots playoff game with the Maryland Blue Crabs has been rained out Friday night. (Photo: ~File) CONNECT TWEET LINKEDIN COMMENT EMAIL MORE 
Friday eveningâ€™s Game 3 of the Atlantic League Championship Series between the Somerset Patriots and the Southern Maryland Blue Crabs has been postponed due to rain. 
Due to inclement weather in the Maryland region, the contest will now take place tomorrow at 6:35 p.m. at Regency Furniture Stadium. 
The best-of-five series is tied at 1-1 as Southern Maryland took the opener with a 7-3 victory, but Somerset salvaged a split at TD Bank Ballpark winning the following night 7-2. 
The Patriots are looking for their sixth Atlantic League Championship. The Blue Crabs are searching for their first title.
